 Michele|title=Mexico and the Foreign Policy of Napoleon III|publisher= Palgrave|year= 2001|url= https://www.questia.com/library/102567418/mexico-and-the-foreign-policy-of-napoleon-iii| isbn=978-0333793022}}\n*  Golicz, Roman. \u201cNapoleon III, Lord Palmerston and the Entente Cordiale.\u201d ''History Today'' 50#12 (December 2000): 10\u201317\n* {{cite book |last=Guedalla|first= Philip|title = The Second Empire |year=1923 |url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.95986/page/n11|asin=B00085CK6Y}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Pinkney|first= David H.|title=Napoleon III's Transformation of Paris: The Origins and Development of the Idea|journal= Journal of Modern History|year= 1955|volume= 27|issue= 2 |pages=125\u201334 |jstor=1874987|doi= 10.1086/237781}}\n* {{cite book|last=Pinkney|first = David H. |title=Napoleon III and the Rebuilding of Paris |publisher=Princeton University Press|year=1958|isbn=0-691-00768-3}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Plessis|first=Alain|title=The Rise and Fall of the Second Empire 1852\u20131871|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1988|isbn = 978-0521358569}}\n* Price, Roger. ''The French Second Empire, An Anatomy of Political Power'' Cambridge UP, 2001), 507 pp.\n* {{cite book| last= Williams| first = Roger L. |title=Gaslight and shadow: The World of Napoleon III 1851-1870|publisher = Macmillan & Co Ltd| location = New York |year =1957| url=  https://archive.org/details/gaslightshadowwo00will| asin = B001NHPZ72}}\n* Wolf, John B.  ''France: 1815 to the Present'' (1963)  pp- 212\u2013341\n* {{cite book| last= Zeldin|first= Theodore |title=The Political System of Napoleon III |publisher =Macmillan & Co Ltd|location=New York|year= 1958|url=https://archive.org/stream/in.ernet.dli.2015.110509/2015.110509.The-Political-System-Of-Napoleon-Iii_djvu.txt|asin= B0000CJYLM}}\n\n{{refend}}\n\n===Primary sources===\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* T. W. Evans, ''Memoirs of the Second French Empire'', (New York, 1905)\n* [[Marie-Clotilde-Elisabeth Louise de Riquet, comtesse de Mercy-Argenteau]], ''The Last Love of an Emperor'': reminiscences of the Comtesse Louise de Mercy-Argenteau, n\u00e9e Princesse de Caraman-Chimay, describing her association with the Emperor Napoleon III and the social and political part she played at the close of the [[Second French Empire|Second Empire]] (Doubleday, Page & Co., 1926).\n{{refend}}\n\n===In French ===\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* Anceau, Eric (2008), ''Napol\u00e9on III, un Saint-Simon \u00e0 cheval'', Paris, Tallandier.\n* Choisel, Francis (2015),  '' La Deuxi\u00e8me R\u00e9publique et le Second Empire au jour le jour'', chronologie \u00e9rudite d\u00e9taill\u00e9e, Paris, CNRS Editions.\n*{{Citation|last=Girard |first=Louis |title=Napol\u00e9on III |location=Paris |publisher=Fayard |year=1986 |isbn=978-2-01-27-9098-8}}\n* {{Citation| last=Milza |first=Pierre |title=Napol\u00e9on III |location=Paris|publisher=Tempus |year=2006 |isbn=978-2-262-02607-3}}\n*{{Citation|last=S\u00e9guin|first=Philippe|title=Louis Napol\u00e9on Le Grand|publisher=Bernard Grasset|location=Paris|year=1990|isbn=978-2-246-42951-7|url=https://archive.org/details/louisnapoleonleg00segu}}\n* Tulard, Jean (dir.), (1995), ''Dictionnaire du Second Empire'', Paris, Fayard, 1348 p.\n{{refend}}\n\n===Additional reading===\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite book|last=Bresler|first=Fenton|title=Napoleon III: A Life|publisher=Harper Collins|location=London|year=1999|url=https://archive.org/details/napoleoniiilife00bres|isbn=978-0-00-255787-0}}\n* {{cite book|last=Baguley|first= David|title= Napoleon III and His Regime: An Extravaganza|publisher= LSU Press| year=2000|isbn=978-0807126240}}\n* {{cite book|last=Bury|first= J. P. T. |title=Napoleon III and the Second Empire |publisher= Perennial Library |year=1964|asin=B0032OSXA0}}\n* {{cite book|last=Case|first= Lynn M. |title=French Opinion on War and Diplomacy during the Second Empire| publisher=University of Pennsylvania Press |year=1954|isbn=978-0374913021}}\n* {{cite book | last=Cobban 